snippet.textDisplay: I think we can all agree that Minecraft's golden ages were from 2009 to 2011ish (which was the first alpha release to about version 1.2) It was something special in those years. Nowadays it's all just mass produced mini games, YouTube videos and internet trolling. I miss the days when Minecraft was just about building and screwing around with some friends. It feels tainted now...
snippet.textOriginal: I think we can all agree that Minecraft's golden ages were from 2009 to 2011ish (which was the first alpha release to about version 1.2) It was something special in those years. Nowadays it's all just mass produced mini games, YouTube videos and internet trolling. I miss the days when Minecraft was just about building and screwing around with some friends. It feels tainted now...
